This #WorldEnvironmentDay join Massimo Bottura  UN Environment Programme and be part of #GenerationRestoration to help change the world in a SNAP!
Nature is our solution to achieve the #SustainbleDevelopmentGoals and kick-start action for a better world. 

You can start in a SNAP by making smart choices at home and what you put on your plate:
1. Support local farms
2. Plant a garden
3. Fill your refrigerator with seasonal ingredients
4. Purchase just what you need and preserve what is leftover
5. Create Plant-Rich recipes

Together, we can be the first generation to reimagine, recreate and restore nature and rebuild the ecosystems that safeguard our health and well-being.
Join #GenerationRestoration and show us how you will change the world in a SNAP @unep

node.text:
Ciao a tutti! I’m excited to share the prep video from our special #nzkitchenquarantine
We had as much fun with the prep as we did with assembling and enjoying the meal. New Zealand food and wine is really something! 
Thanks again to our new friends for your beautiful products: @Manukahealthnz @Marisco_Wines @OraKingSalmon @puresouth_uk @zespri_kiwifruit_italia 
Grazie mille to our amazing guest @jacindaardern - such a warm and lovely message. I so look forward to visiting you and my new friends in New Zealand some day soon! And to my friend @galettigram, thank you for dialling in - great to catch up and see your beautiful BBQ dinner!

For my recipes from this special night and to have a chance to win a New Zealand food hamper, visit: www.newzealandbusiness.nz/KQ

@nzte @taikawaititi @peakybuzzout @austin.brick

node.text:
Ciao a tutti, what a fun night! We loved cooking with premium New Zealand food and wine tonight for this special #nzkitchenquarantine • New Zealand food and beverages come from distinctive local environments, with pure climates, soils, and ocean. It was a privilege to taste New Zealand here in Italy tonight. We share many similarities when it comes to our food and wine – as well as caring for people and place. Both countries are known for the beauty of our landscapes and the friendliness and integrity of our people.• I cooked tonight using products from @manukahealthnz @marisco_wines @orakingsalmon @puresouth_uk @zespri_kiwifruit_italia 
Thanks to my friends @jacindaardern and @galettigram – I’d love to visit you both in New Zealand when things are back to normal @nzte • For my recipes from tonight and to win a food hamper: https://www.newzealandbusiness.nz/kq

#nzkitchenquarantine #kitchenquarantine 
#newzealandfoodandwine #kiwiquarantine

This #WorldEnvironmentDay join Massimo Bottura  UN Environment Programme and be part of #GenerationRestoration to help change the world in a SNAP!
Nature is our solution to achieve the #SustainbleDevelopmentGoals and kick-start action for a better world. 

You can start in a SNAP by making smart choices at home and what you put on your plate:
1. Support local farms
2. Plant a garden
3. Fill your refrigerator with seasonal ingredients
4. Purchase just what you need and preserve what is leftover
5. Create Plant-Rich recipes

Together, we can be the first generation to reimagine, recreate and restore nature and rebuild the ecosystems that safeguard our health and well-being.
Join #GenerationRestoration and show us how you will change the world in a SNAP @unep

WHERE OTHERS SEE IMPERFECTIONS - I SEE BEAUTY
as a very proud UN ambassador, I want to share these new numbers about world food waste. 
In 2019 - 690 Million people were affected by hunger. 3 Billion unable to afford a healthy diet.  The numbers continue to rise with COVID-19.
We Wasted: 931 million tonnes of food sold to households, retailers, restaurants and other food services.  17% of ALL FOOD AVAILABLE AT CONSUMER LEVEL.
This month @UNEP released the Food Waste Index Report 2021 supporting action for SDG 12.3.  
Friends... this is a CALL TO ACT.

See the report at: 
https://www.unep.org/resources/report/unep-food-waste-index-report-2021

@UNEP @UNFOODSYSTEMS @foodforsoul_it 

#foodwaste #Actnow #ThinkEatSave
